Hatice Aslan
Hatice Aslan (born 1962 in Sivas, Turkey) is a Turkish actress who starred in
Nuri Bilge Ceylan's 2008 film "Üç Maymun (The Three Monkeys)", for which Ceylan won the best director award at the 2008 Cannes Film Festival. Aslan was seen as a strong contender for the best actress award at the festival.
Hatice Aslan shared the Adana Golden Boll International Film Festival's Best Actress Award in 2011 together with Görkem Yeltan for her role in "Vücut".
